    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.32-33_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">32</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>January 29</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr.N<del>N</del><add>e</add>ihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am sorry I have been so long in writing but business has kept me very busy. I had a wonderful time visiting you and your daughter and her family and am only sorry that it had to be for such a short time.</p>
                
                <p>I read carefull Mrs. Aly's thesis and was quite impressed. She did gather an overwhelming store of material and used it quite well. It must have been great fun for you to look back at Neihardt the young man, Neihardt the <del>x</del><add>c</add>ritic, and Ne<del>o</del><add>i</add>hardt the lecturer. From the book though it vseems<sic>seems</sic> that in most cases the pattern of your thinking remained along the same lines.</p>
                
                <p>If I have any quarrel with Mrs Aly's work it is one that is not her responsibility. The academic requirements for any such work require a certain style and adherence to th<del>e</del><add>a</add>tstyle<sic>that style</sic> causes h<del>r</del><add>e</add>r to lose facets of your warmth and humanity. Cold quotes stating your ideas can never replace warm descriptive passages about you and your thinking. This I hop<del>w</del><add>e</add> she will remedy in her biography I plan to keep the thesis for another 3 weeks or so while I try to work out an articl<del>a</del><add>e</add> about you. I hopw<sic>hope</sic> this will not cause you any inconvenience.</p>
               
                <p>Take good care of yourself and you will be hearing from me in the near future.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely</salute> 
                    
                    <signed>Bob Leaf</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
